  %h1 Transforms
%section
  %pre
    %code
      :preserve
        .element{
          transform: scale(.5);
        }
  %p.note
    Transforms modify the appearance of an element (scale, rotate, transalate,
    skewâ€¦) without affecting the surrounding elements. They are quite useful for
    adding interaction and effects.

%section
  .codepen(data-height="400" data-editable="true" data-theme-id="0" data-slug-hash="XWrgYKw" data-default-tab="css,result" data-user="htmlboy")
  %p.note
    The <code>scale()</code> transform will change the size of the element
    proportionally to the number between parentheses. If we only want to modify
    the width or height, we can use <code>scaleX()</code> or <code>scaleY()</code>.


%section
  .codepen(data-height="400" data-editable="true" data-theme-id="0" data-slug-hash="PoYjaOO" data-default-tab="css,result" data-user="htmlboy")
  %p.note
    With <code>rotate()</code> we can make an element rotate a number of degrees
    (with the <code>deg</code> unit).



%section
  .codepen(data-height="400" data-editable="true" data-theme-id="0" data-slug-hash="gOYRKvX" data-default-tab="css,result" data-user="htmlboy")
  %p.note
    With <code>translate()</code> we can indicate the displacement in the X axis
    and in the Y axis of an element, using two values separated by a comma. If
    we only want to move on a single axis, we can use <code>translateX()</code> or
    <code> translateY()</code>.


%section
  .codepen(data-height="400" data-editable="true" data-theme-id="0" data-slug-hash="zYOzaMG" data-default-tab="css,result" data-user="htmlboy")
  %p.note
    With <code>skewX()</code> and <code>skewY()</code> we can deform an element
    on the X or Y axis a number of degrees (<code>deg</code>).

%section
  .codepen(data-height="400" data-editable="true" data-theme-id="0" data-slug-hash="wvweXZY" data-default-tab="css,result" data-user="htmlboy")
  %p.note
    We can assign several transformations, separated by spaces. In addition, we can control the origin from which the transformations are performed with the <code>transform-origin</code> property.

